{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we assume that a verification method is provided and focus arXiv:2511.21531v1 [cs.LG] 26 Nov 2025 on the integration of this safety verification with model-based RL for discrete action spaces.Additionally, let us discuss the existing literature on safeguards for RL in discrete spaces in more detail, which can be split into safeguards obtaining probabilistic guarantees [3], [4], [10], [15]- [17] and hard guarantees [2], [10], [11], [18].",
    "For instance, He et al. [3] propose a probabilistic shield that samples trajectories to determine the risk probability and interfere if the predicted probability is above a defined threshold.",
    "To produce the trajectory, the current policy is iteratively executed in a latent space, i.e., with a learned environment model.",
    "Goodall et al. [4] generalize this work and derive probability bounds for constraint violation with learned and true environment models.",
    "They perform evaluations on five Atari games and show that their advancements lead to higher performance and fewer violations."
  ],
